## ðŸ“‹ ALL COMMANDS - Week 1 Complete Reference (With Explanations)

### 1. Docker + docker-compose Setup
cd /home/somesh/DVP/docker-nginx-app # Change to project directory
docker build -t somesha/nginx-app:v1 . # Build Docker image, tag as somesha/nginx-app:v1, . = current directory
docker run -d --name my-nginx --network host somesha/nginx-app:v1 # Run container in background (-d), name it my-nginx, host network
docker compose up -d # Start docker-compose services in background
docker compose logs # View real-time logs from compose services
docker compose down # Stop and remove compose services
curl http://127.0.0.1 # Test website locally (localhost)
docker ps # List running containers

text

### 2. Docker Hub Manual Push
docker login -u somesha # Login to Docker Hub with username somesha
docker build -t somesha/nginx-app:latest . # Build and tag image as latest version
docker push somesha/nginx-app:latest # Upload image to Docker Hub repository
docker pull somesha/nginx-app:latest # Download latest image from Docker Hub

text

### 3. GitHub Actions CI/CD Setup
mkdir -p .github/workflows # Create directories for GitHub Actions workflow
nano .github/workflows/ci.yml # Edit/create workflow YAML file
git add .github/workflows/ci.yml # Stage workflow file for commit
git commit -m "ci: add docker build-push workflow" # Commit with descriptive message
git push origin main # Upload changes to GitHub main branch

text

### 4. AWS EC2 Deployment
ssh -i your-key.pem ubuntu@3.89.223.3 # SSH connect to EC2 using private key
sudo apt update # Update package lists
sudo apt install docker.io -y # Install Docker
sudo systemctl start docker # Start Docker service
sudo usermod -aG docker ubuntu # Add ubuntu user to docker group
docker login -u somesha # Login to Docker Hub on EC2
docker pull somesha/nginx-app:latest # Pull your image from Docker Hub
docker run -d -p 80:80 --name my-nginx --restart unless-stopped somesha/nginx-app:latest # Run container: background, port 80, auto-restart

text

### 5. Git Workflow (Professional)
git checkout -b feature/ci-cd # Create and switch to new feature branch
git add . # Stage all changes
git commit -m "feat: update" # Commit with Conventional Commits message
git checkout main # Switch back to main branch
git merge feature/ci-cd # Merge feature branch into main
git pull --no-rebase origin main # Pull remote changes and merge (safe)
git push origin main # Push to GitHub
git branch -d feature/ci-cd # Delete local feature branch

text

### 6. Monitoring & Debugging
docker logs my-nginx # View container logs
docker exec -it my-nginx sh # Enter running container shell (interactive)
docker ps -a # List ALL containers (running + stopped)
docker stop my-nginx # Gracefully stop container
docker rm my-nginx # Remove stopped container
docker images # List local Docker images
docker history somesha/nginx-app:latest # Show image layers and sizes

text

### 7. Full End-to-End Demo Flow
1. Make code change
echo "<h1>Updated $(date)</h1>" > app/index.html # Update HTML with timestamp

2. Commit and push (triggers CI/CD)
git add app/index.html
git commit -m "feat: update homepage timestamp"
git push origin main # GitHub Actions starts automatically!

3. Verify pipeline
Watch: https://github.com/Somesha-honnali/docker-nginx-app/actions
Check: https://hub.docker.com/r/somesha/nginx-app/tags
Live: http://3.89.223.3 # Refresh to see changes!
text

